while fast and fast.next:
    slow = slow.next
    fast = fast.next.next

# slow is middle OR meet point

2️⃣ FIXED DISTANCE PATTERN ⭐ (IMPORTANT)
(Fast starts first, Slow follows)
👉 Used for:

Nth node from end

Kth node from last

Remove from end

🧠 When to use?

Question says:

from end

last k

one pass

✅ BASIC TEMPLATE
slow = fast = head

# create distance
for _ in range(k):
    fast = fast.next

# move together
while fast:
    slow = slow.next
    fast = fast.next

# slow is answer

3️⃣ MEET / COMPARE PATTERN
(Two pointers meet or compare)
👉 Used for:

Palindrome linked list

Intersection of two lists

🧠 When to use?

Question says:

palindrome

intersection

✅ BASIC TEMPLATE
p1 = head1
p2 = head2

while p1 != p2:
    p1 = p1.next if p1 else head2
    p2 = p2.next if p2 else head1

return p1

